r1261 | tbreina | 2009-08-17 18:57:08 -0400 (Mon, 17 Aug 2009) | 1 line

integer to longint didn't fix the big IDValues. I think the problem was that wxAuiBar had a GetIDValue that wasn't returning anything. So the IDE was grabbing whatever value was in the integer space it had allocated in memory. I forced it to return 0 (which is consistent with other non-visual controls). Problem appears to be solved now. Also, changed all the types from longint to integer just in case.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r1260 | tbreina | 2009-08-17 16:14:35 -0400 (Mon, 17 Aug 2009) | 1 line

Added GExperts path using $(PROGRAMFILES) to search path
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r1259 | tbreina | 2009-08-17 14:43:35 -0400 (Mon, 17 Aug 2009) | 2 lines

Changed IDValue from integer to longint for consistency. I'm hoping that this is the cause of the "large IDValue bug" we've been seeing sporadically. In some places in the source code, IDValue was declared integer and in others it was declared longint. Ideally, it only needs to be integer, but there were far more places to change from longint to integer than vice versa so I went with the path of least changes.

