r1072 | tbreina | 2008-09-22 01:01:14 -0400 (Mon, 22 Sep 2008) | 32 lines

Updated NSIS installer files. We're now trying to install all of the files via DevPaks. This way it should be easier to uninstall/update them.

The following devpaks should be included in your install build directory (under a subdirectory called Packages).

binutils.devpak
devcpp_examples.devpak
devcpphelp.devpak
gcc-core.devpak
gcc-g++.devpak
gdb.devpak
Language.devpak
make.devpak
mingw-runtime.devpak
Programming with wxDev-C++.devpak
Templates.devpak
win32api.devpak
wxdevcpp_rc1.devpak
wxWidgets_common.devpak
wxWidgets_contrib_common.devpak
wxWidgets_extras_common.devpak
wxWidgets_gcc.devpak
wxWidgets_gcc_contrib.devpak
wxWidgets_gcc_extras.devpak
wxWidgets_samples.devpak
wxWidgets_vc2005.devpak
wxWidgets_vc2005_contrib.devpak
wxWidgets_vc2008.devpak
wxWidgets_vc2008.devpak
wxWidgets_vc2008_contrib.devpak

Alternatively, we can modify the installer to download these devpaks from the webupdate server.

