r760 | lowjoel | 2006-12-21 22:07:17 -0500 (Thu, 21 Dec 2006) | 5 lines

First revision of forms for Vista.
-Forms' Ok/Cancel buttons have a standard dimension. If there are only OK and cancel buttons, both buttons will have a 5px space between buttons. Following Vista Human Interface Guidelines all button will be 75px by 23px. Ok and Cancel buttons with bitmaps attached will be assigned 80px by 23px. If there are OK, cancel and Help buttons, the OK and cancel buttons will follow the above rule, and the help button will be 75px by 23px, the spacing between the OK and the help button being 15px.
-XPMenu.Active - I optimized the old code by directly assigning the calue of devData.XPTheme to the XPMenu.Active property, this saves an If statement
-TWinControl.DesktopFont. All forms now have this value so that under every OS the proper font will be used and we will not stick to MS Sans Serif (which will make things look weird). Testing under Vista and XP is mandatory before next release as some forms may have excessive text (e.g LangFrm.dfm) and may require form tweaking.
-TControl.ParentFont. ALWAYS set it to true. This is so that controls will use the font of the parent control, and if you follow the parent-child relationship far enough we hopefully can trace it to the screen font, which is MS Sans Serif 8pt under pre-XP systems, Tahoma 8pt under XP, Segoe UI 9pt under Vista. If controls need special formatting (e.g. underline, bold) or special font colors (e.g. AboutForm's links) set them dynamically by code.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r759 | lowjoel | 2006-12-21 01:09:59 -0500 (Thu, 21 Dec 2006) | 3 lines

-Replace all the text fields in the CPU form with a list-view (which hence can take more registers if we wish to include other registers in the future
-Replaced the 'u' command for disassembly with 'uf' for CDB - this way the whole function is disassembled, like GDB's behaviour
-Added support for the 3 other x86 registers, FS, GS and EFLAGS.
