r755 | lowjoel | 2006-12-20 06:53:55 -0500 (Wed, 20 Dec 2006) | 12 lines

-Removed the properties for handling the position and sizing of the controls on the main form - the new docking system does that for us.
-Added a new function that will execute make and ask if all the files are up to date. This can be called from TCompiler.UpToDate, and requires that the type of compilation be a project and that a valid project object is given (only projects require makefiles anyway)
-Removed the "Debug" sheet on the project inspector - it should be the "Watches" sheet in the debug tab
-Associate image lists for all the context menus - having icons on the context menus add clarity and allows quick glancing without needing to read the label most of the time
-Removed a few old menu items in the View menu that pertained to the showing and hiding of the report window (which are now distributed to dockable windows) as well as floating and docking the project inspector (the project inspector can dock and float itself without extra code now)
-Removed an old "dead" function (ELDesigner1Notification)
-Removed all the supporting code for the message sheet; they are now all tabs and thus renders most code obsolete, others have been ported
-Rudimentary support for updating the dockable windows' images. The code will need revision in the future because JVCL caches the images and does not update them
-Implemented tab position for the dockable windows - change it using the "Tab position" value in the encironment settings dialog
-The moment a new project is created the caption of the main IDE can be updated; there is no need to wait for a save operation
-Instead of forcibly recompiling the project before a debug session, just ask make if we are up to date. This keeps version numbers correct and does not excessively increment them
-Use generic functions for the "copy" and "clear" functions for the message windows (compiler, compiler output, find results etc)
