r700 | tbreina | 2006-11-22 14:42:11 -0500 (Wed, 22 Nov 2006) | 2 lines

A user had a 6.9 project that wasn't working in 6.10. The problem was with spaces in the directory name. 
ExeOutput and ObjOutput directory names don't like spaces. When we import a 6.9 (or earlier) project, we set it's default profile name to "Default Profile". This puts a space in the subdirectories for ExeOutput and ObjOutput. To prevent this, I've add a new string function called strRemoveBadCharacters which removes spaces and other offending characters (e.g. quotes) from those directory names.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r699 | tbreina | 2006-11-22 13:44:20 -0500 (Wed, 22 Nov 2006) | 1 line

