r544 | gururamnath | 2006-10-28 13:05:33 -0400 (Sat, 28 Oct 2006) | 11 lines

The patch fixes the following issues:
1)if the Object path and Exe output path are empty the profile name is assigned.
2)The ViewID dlg will highlight the IDs with duplicate values and we also have the ability to filter IDs with zero value.
3)Fix for the WinSDKDir function as per tony's suggestion.
4)The Browse button events for Exe and Obj path are modified to make sure short directory name is used.
5)Support for WxBitmapComboBox (Since this is just a copy of wxCombobox, I just added it - took 5 mins to complete it) 6)Finally support for Default Event Creation on Double Click. (This is just a preliminary support so it will just open the first one) 7)Previously the CalanderCtrl accepts others controls, now it acts as a proper non-container component.
8)Fixed the crash when the CalanderCtrl is deleted from the Form.
9)Fixed the erratic code generation for PassWordEntry Dlg.
10)Reorganized Some labels and added the wxbook info in the Aboutbox.
11)Conversion of 2.5 and 2.6 lib names to 2.7 libraries.

