r228 | tbreina | 2005-09-25 11:20:46 -0400 (Sun, 25 Sep 2005) | 15 lines

1. Modified Designer Options Form - There's now 2 tabs: designer options and code
 generation options. User can now switch which string function he wants for passing strings (wxT, _(), or _T()). This will help with string internationalization.

2. Potential fix in CodeCompletion.pas for an out-of-bounds error during code completion. Basically, typing msg.Printf( _T("test") _T("test2") will cause the code
 completion to generate a fatal run-time error. From looking at the inherited devcpp
 code, I think this is because it is trying to access a string at an index < 1 (which,
 of course, is out-of-bounds). I put some if-then statements to prevent this. Still
 waiting for the dev-cpp guys to comment on the change.

3. -1 Support - Added support in wxButton.pas to allow for the user to set the height
 and width to -1. The buttonsize in the designer stays the same, but a -1 is passed
 to the code generator. Also, a check to see if the top or left positions are < 0
 (which is out of bounds). If there are no problems with the code, then this should
 be added to the remaining visual components.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
