------------------------------------------------------------------------
r117 | tbreina | 2005-04-30 01:36:27 -0400 (Sat, 30 Apr 2005) | 8 lines

1. & Code - All strings (e.g. ToolTips, Captions, Value properties) now go through GetCppString() before they are written.  Typically, all of these strings will be passed as text using wxT("STRINGVALUE") where STRINGVALUE is the string that the user typed into the property. However, if the string begins with an ampersand (&), it will be passed as a literal (without the & of course). This will allow users to specify variable names and even functions or code to be passed to text properties.

2. THIS_DIALOG_STYLE - The templates are now changed so that THIS_DIALOG_STYLE is no longer used as the define for window styles. Instead, the constant name will be %CLASSNAME%_STYLE where %CLASSNAME% is replaced by the name of the window class. For backward compatibility, the IDE scans for the name of the constant and keeps it. So if THIS_DIALOG_STYLE is already defined, then it will keep it. Also, if the user wishes to change the name to something else, they may do so and the code will use the user-defined name.

3. Menu bugs (#1167551, 1094889, 1065862)  - Mal fixed these. Submenus should now be generated correctly.

4. Style options bug (#1189349, 1176465, ) - wxButton, wxBitmapButton,  wxTextCtrl (Memo and Edit), wxCheckBox, wxListBox, wxNotebook, wxOpenFileDialog, wxSaveFileDialog, wxProgressDialog, and wxMessageDialog style options were corrected. wxListbox styles wxLB_SINGLE/wxLB_MULTIPLE/wxLB_EXTENDED now displayed as a dropdown listbox (so they are mutually exclusive). I'd like to eventually have these placed with the rest of the wxListbox styles.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
